## M2 — Pitch SVG + formation picker UI built

### New files
- `src/lib/formations.ts` — pure module: `Formation` / `FormationSlot` types, per-format catalogs (SOCCER 5..11-aside, FUTSAL 5-aside), assignment helpers, slot-compat map.
- `src/components/FormationPitch.tsx` — replaces the old in-file `TeamFormation`. Renders the picker, the SVG pitch, and the auto+manual assignment.

### Updated wiring
- `MatchdayAvailability.tsx` — drops the in-file 5-formation list + bucket-row distribution + `<TeamFormation>`. New props `ballType?: 'SOCCER' | 'FUTSAL' | null` and `playerFormat?: number | null` thread to `<FormationPitch>` for both the "Who Played" (past) and "Who else is coming?" (upcoming) sections.
- `ClassicLeagueHomepage.tsx` — adds the same two props and forwards them down.
- `Dashboard.tsx` — at the `<ClassicLeagueHomepage>` call site: `ballType={league?.ballType ?? leagueDetails?.ballType ?? null}` + `playerFormat={leagueDetails?.playerFormat ?? null}`. Both sources already exist on the server-side payload (`league` is the prisma row select including `ballType`; `leagueDetails` carries `playerFormat`).

### Coordinate system
Normalised `x ∈ [0, 1]` (left→right) and `y ∈ [0, 1]` (own goal→opp goal). The pitch SVG keeps the existing 100×133 viewBox and dark-green stripes. Slots position absolutely via `top: (1 - slot.y) * 100%` / `left: slot.x * 100%` with a `-translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2` to centre. Row y bands: GK=0.06, DEF=0.27, DM=0.42, MID=0.55, AM=0.66, FWD=0.85.

### Picker UX choice
**Horizontal scrollable strip** of formation pills (text-only, e.g. `4-3-3`, `1-2-1 (Diamond)`). Why not thumbnail grid:
- The pitch directly below already renders the *active* formation in full — a thumbnail strip would be redundant chrome on a small mobile screen.
- 5 short pills fit a 360 px viewport inline; longer labels (futsal `1-2-1 (Diamond)`, `4-0 (Rotational)`) get a horizontal-scroll fallback via `overflow-x-auto`.
- Matches the existing pre-v1.83.0 picker shape (`text-[8px] uppercase tracking-widest` pills with team-colour active state) so this isn't a chrome shock to existing users.

The active pill highlights with `teamColor + '55'` background (same convention as the old TeamFormation).

### localStorage
Selected formation persists per `(ballType, playerCount)` tuple under `t9l-formation:<ballType>:<n>`. Hydrates on mount, falls back to `formations[0]?.code` (the catalog's conventional default).

### Next: M3 (assignment + slot-compat map for review)

## M3 — Multi-role assignment algorithm + slot-compat map

### Algorithm — `assignPlayersToFormation()` in `src/lib/formations.ts`
Greedy scarcity-first:
1. Players with `positions.length === 0` skip the assignment loop and surface in `playersWithoutPositions` (UI hints "fill in your profile").
2. For each formation slot, build a candidate set: all eligible players whose `positions` include any code that the slot's code accepts.
3. While unfilled slots with non-empty candidate sets remain:
   a. Pick the unfilled slot with the FEWEST candidates (>0). Tie-break by slot index.
   b. Within that slot, pick the player with the FEWEST other compatible slots (least flexible — save the polyvalent players for the slots that desperately need them). Tie-break by player id (lexicographic) for determinism.
   c. Mark the slot+player assigned. Remove the player from every other slot's candidate set.
4. Remaining eligible players → `unassignedPlayers` (rendered as "Subs (N)").
5. Slots with no candidate at all stay empty (rendered as a dashed circle); the UI surfaces a `"N slots have no candidate available."` line.

Complexity: `O(slots² × players)` — for ≤11×~25 it runs in microseconds. Hungarian-algorithm overkill, per the user spec.

### Slot-compat map — direction: PLAYER position → set of SLOT codes the player can fill

#### Soccer (12-code vocabulary)
| Player code | Slots it can fill                | Rationale                                         |
|-------------|----------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| `GK`        | `GK`                             | Strict.                                           |
| `LB`        | `LB`                             | Per user spec — strict (no auto-shift to CB/RB). |
| `CB`        | `CB`, `DM`                       | CB→DM common in build-up (false-CB / regista).   |
| `RB`        | `RB`                             | Mirror of LB — strict.                            |
| `LM`        | `LM`, `LW`                       | Per user spec.                                    |
| `DM`        | `DM`, `CM`, `CB`                 | DM↔CB swap on overload; DM→CM box-to-box pivot. |
| `CM`        | `DM`, `CM`, `CAM`                | Per user spec.                                    |
| `CAM`       | `CAM`, `CM`, `ST`                | False-9 / second-striker drop in.                |
| `RM`        | `RM`, `RW`                       | Mirror of LM.                                     |
| `LW`        | `LW`, `LM`, `ST`                 | Wide forward → wide mid / centre forward.        |
| `ST`        | `ST`, `CAM`                      | Centre forward swaps; doesn't shift wide.        |
| `RW`        | `RW`, `RM`, `ST`                 | Mirror of LW.                                     |

#### Futsal (4-code vocabulary)
| Player code | Slots it can fill                | Rationale                                         |
|-------------|----------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| `GK`        | `GK`                             | Strict.                                           |
| `FIXO`      | `FIXO`, `ALA`                    | FIXO can step into ALA on the rotational system. |
| `ALA`       | `ALA`, `FIXO`, `PIVOT`           | Most flexible — wing/midfield bridge.            |
| `PIVOT`     | `PIVOT`, `ALA`                   | PIVOT can drop to ALA when teams play 4-0.       |

The 4-0 (Rotational) futsal formation models its 4 outfield slots as `ALA` since that's the most permissive code — any FIXO/ALA/PIVOT player can fill them.

### Surface-back to user
The strict cases (`LB`, `RB`, `GK`) intentionally do NOT auto-shift to nearby roles. If you'd rather LB-tagged players also fill the LB or CB slot when the formation has no other LB candidate, say the word and I'll widen those entries — would be a 2-line change.

### Next: M4 (edge cases + manual override UX — most already implemented in FormationPitch)

## M4 — Edge cases + manual override UX

### Edge case handling
| Case                                                         | Handling                                                                                              |
|--------------------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| No confirmations yet                                         | "No confirmations yet" italic text — same as pre-v1.83.0.                                             |
| Player has no positions on file                              | Skipped from assignment loop; surfaced in a footer line: `"N players have no position on file."`     |
| Fewer available players than slots                           | Unfilled slots render as dashed-ring placeholders. Counter line: `"N slots have no candidate available."` |
| More players than slots (overflow)                           | Bench section "Subs (N)" with name pills (small + position chip). Auto-assignment respects scarcity, so the most-flexible players go to subs first. |
| Formation has no candidates for a slot type                  | Same as "fewer players than slots" — empty dashed circle, counter line.                                |
| `(ballType, playerFormat)` has no catalog (e.g. SOCCER/4)    | Falls back to a flat name-list with an amber italic hint: `"No formations defined for this league format yet."` |
| `playerFormat` is null (legacy league row)                   | Catalog returns empty; same fallback as above.                                                        |
| `ballType` is null                                           | Defaults to `'SOCCER'` for catalog + slot-compat (Tennozu's default). Logged once via the type union. |

### Manual override UX
**SlotPickerSheet** — bottom-sheet on mobile, centred dialog on `sm+`:
- Triggered by tapping any slot (filled OR empty).
- Lists every confirmed-going player. Each row shows name + their position codes; non-compatible candidates get an amber `"OUT OF POSITION"` chip but stay tappable (admins know best — the algorithm shouldn't refuse a manual override).
- Currently-assigned player is highlighted with `bg-electric-violet/20`.
- "Clear slot" button below the list (only when a player is currently assigned).
- Backdrop + ESC + "Close" button all dismiss.
- Manual choices are stored in a local `overrides: Record<slotIdx, playerId | null>` map merged with the auto-assignment. Picking a player who was already auto-placed elsewhere automatically wipes that other placement (no duplicates).
- Overrides reset when the formation code changes or the confirmed player set changes (different slot indexes / different roster invalidates the choices).

